"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-sport-othersport-1928911-Olympics-LIVE-IOC-Olympics-2024-Paris-Games\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  Olympics 2024mania is well underway, with the action coming thick and fast over the next couple of weeks.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 107, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening ceremony took place on Friday asathletes sailed down the River Seinein the pouring rain.\", \"from\": 108, \"to\": 208, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Australia led the medal table overnightafter clinching three golds, including the women's 4 x 100m freestyle relay in the swimming pool.\", \"from\": 210, \"to\": 346, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 210, \"end\": 219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.912969686329035, \"rank\": 0.08130857379653594, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"China claimed three golds on the first full day of action, with the USA and France both getting their hands on one gold.\", \"from\": 348, \"to\": 468, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 348, \"end\": 353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9610757285606829, \"rank\": 0.04049874503856845, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 416, \"end\": 419, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999988025709065, \"rank\": 1.0453019796415644e-06, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 424, \"end\": 430, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9998118935900596, \"rank\": 0.00018803918111710044, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Great Britain will be aiming for scores of medals in the French capital after winning 22 golds, 20 silvers and 22 bronze medals at the Tokyo Games three years ago.\", \"from\": 470, \"to\": 633, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 470, \"end\": 483, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999993260410063, \"rank\": 4.615191623296616e-07, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 527, \"end\": 533, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9998168469854368, \"rank\": 0.0001787952387310307, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And Team GB claimed their first opening day medal since 2004 when divers Yasmin Harper and Scarlett Mew Jensen won bronze in the women's synchronised 3m springboard in Paris following a catastrophe for the Australian duo.\", \"from\": 635, \"to\": 856, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 639, \"end\": 646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7984882362557684e-14, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 726, \"end\": 745, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scarlett_Mew_Jensen\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Scarlett Mew Jensen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scarlett_Mew_Jensen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scarlett_Mew_Jensen\"}, {\"begin\": 803, \"end\": 808, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9436973583780052e-29, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 841, \"end\": 851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9997174385464953, \"rank\": 0.00020121415676971468, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Great Britain's Anna Henderson later won a silver in the women's road race time trial.\", \"from\": 857, \"to\": 943, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 857, \"end\": 870, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999993260410063, \"rank\": 4.615191623296616e-07, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 873, \"end\": 887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Henderson\", \"score\": 0.9999958972005097, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anna Henderson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Henderson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Henderson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Express Sport will have all the latest stories from the Olympics 2024 throughout the day.\", \"from\": 945, \"to\": 1034, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So stick around and follow all the action in our live blog below.\", \"from\": 1035, \"to\": 1100, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's all we have time for, sadly.\", \"from\": 1102, \"to\": 1137, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We will be back with a new LIVE news blog tomorrow morning to take you through Monday's action.\", \"from\": 1139, \"to\": 1234, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For now, take care!\", \"from\": 1236, \"to\": 1255, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So a reminder of those Team GB medals across the last few days...  Adam Peaty was agonisingly close to Britain's first gold at the Paris Olympics, but secured joint-silver in the men's 100m breaststroke.\", \"from\": 1257, \"to\": 1460, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1280, \"end\": 1287, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7984882362557684e-14, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 1324, \"end\": 1334, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Adam Peaty\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\"}, {\"begin\": 1360, \"end\": 1367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9824737463962118, \"rank\": 0.017838902737359674, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That came after Kimberley Woods won bronze in the women's kayak singles.\", \"from\": 1462, \"to\": 1534, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1478, \"end\": 1493, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kimberley_Woods\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kimberley Woods\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kimberley_Woods\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kimberley_Woods\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On Saturday there was a silver and bronze apiece for cyclist Anna Henderson and diving duo Scarlett Mew Jensen and Yasmin Harper.\", \"from\": 1536, \"to\": 1665, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1597, \"end\": 1611, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Henderson\", \"score\": 0.9999958972005097, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anna Henderson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Henderson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anna_Henderson\"}, {\"begin\": 1627, \"end\": 1646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scarlett_Mew_Jensen\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Scarlett Mew Jensen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scarlett_Mew_Jensen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scarlett_Mew_Jensen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Adam Peaty conducted another emotional interview with theBBCafter having time to reflect on his race.\", \"from\": 1667, \"to\": 1768, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1667, \"end\": 1677, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Adam Peaty\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 29-year-old has faced a battle to get within 0.02 seconds of winning three consecutive Olympic gold medals.\", \"from\": 1770, \"to\": 1881, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have won because my heart is so happy.\", \"from\": 1883, \"to\": 1924, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I can theoretically lose and still feel like I have won,\\\" a tearful Peaty said.\", \"from\": 1925, \"to\": 2004, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I wish I wasn't so emotional but that's my super strength.\", \"from\": 2006, \"to\": 2065, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am looking forward to using this emotion for the rest of my life.\", \"from\": 2066, \"to\": 2133, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Truly enjoy what you do, no matter how hard that trek is.\\\"\", \"from\": 2134, \"to\": 2192, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"An emotional Adam Peaty insisted his post-race tears were for 'happy' reasons after missing out on three consecutive gold medals.\", \"from\": 2194, \"to\": 2323, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2207, \"end\": 2217, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Adam Peaty\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He told the BBC:  \\\"It's been a very long way back and look at the score, you'd have never dreamed of it.\", \"from\": 2325, \"to\": 2429, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2337, \"end\": 2340, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.9999887332758463, \"rank\": 6.109751165195022e-06, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I gave it my all and executed it as well as I could.\", \"from\": 2430, \"to\": 2482, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It did not matter what the time said on the score.\", \"from\": 2483, \"to\": 2533, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am already a winner.\", \"from\": 2534, \"to\": 2556, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am not crying because I have come second, I am crying because it's taken so much to get here.\", \"from\": 2558, \"to\": 2654, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's incredibly hard to win it once, then to win it again, and again.\", \"from\": 2655, \"to\": 2724, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am trying to find new ways to win it.\", \"from\": 2726, \"to\": 2766, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I can race the best in the world and can come joint-second.\", \"from\": 2767, \"to\": 2826, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In my heart I have already won and these are happy tears.\", \"from\": 2827, \"to\": 2884, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can not be upset about that.\\\"\", \"from\": 2885, \"to\": 2918, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Adam Peaty just missed out on a historic third consecutive gold medal in the 100m breaststroke.\", \"from\": 2920, \"to\": 3015, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2920, \"end\": 2930, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Adam Peaty\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The swimmer came joint-second, finishing 0.02 seconds behind Nicolo Martinenghi.\", \"from\": 3017, \"to\": 3097, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3078, \"end\": 3096, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicol\\u00f2_Martinenghi\", \"score\": 0.9999999871770343, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nicolo Martinenghi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicol\\u00f2_Martinenghi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicol\\u00f2_Martinenghi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Peaty spoke of crying \\\"happy tears\\\" afterwards.\", \"from\": 3099, \"to\": 3146, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can read all the reaction byclicking here  Adam Peaty is about to swim for a third consecutive Olympic gold medal.\", \"from\": 3148, \"to\": 3266, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3195, \"end\": 3205, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Adam Peaty\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 29-year-old is the favourite to win the 100m breaststroke.\", \"from\": 3268, \"to\": 3330, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Andy Murrayand Dan Evans remarkably saved five match points and won a thrilling tiebreaker against Taro Daniel and Kei Nishikori.\", \"from\": 3334, \"to\": 3463, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3349, \"end\": 3358, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_J._Evans\", \"score\": 0.9936519797818282, \"rank\": 0.00638857502196987, \"text\": \"Dan Evans\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_J._Evans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_J._Evans\"}, {\"begin\": 3433, \"end\": 3444, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taro_Daniel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Taro Daniel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taro_Daniel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taro_Daniel\"}, {\"begin\": 3449, \"end\": 3462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kei_Nishikori\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kei Nishikori\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kei_Nishikori\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kei_Nishikori\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It means Murray's Olympics adventure continues - and the British duo have a seemingly favourable draw.\", \"from\": 3465, \"to\": 3567, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3474, \"end\": 3480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.6657934415048494e-44, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 3522, \"end\": 3529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9758754467170264, \"rank\": 0.02008087632291979, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bev Priestman has apologised to her Canada players in her first words since receiving a 12-month FIFA suspension.\", \"from\": 3569, \"to\": 3682, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3569, \"end\": 3582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bev_Priestman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bev Priestman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bev_Priestman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bev_Priestman\"}, {\"begin\": 3605, \"end\": 3611, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9993488923467724, \"rank\": 0.0006387933739380703, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 3666, \"end\": 3670, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA\", \"score\": 0.9999980030863228, \"rank\": 1.996917449239428e-06, \"text\": \"FIFA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Canadian women's football head coach was sent home from the tournament after taking responsibility for a drone that flew over a training session being conducted by Olympics opponents New Zealand.\", \"from\": 3684, \"to\": 3883, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3688, \"end\": 3696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.6234966686467387, \"rank\": 0.6038578075646545, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}, {\"begin\": 3871, \"end\": 3882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9219317736524876, \"rank\": 0.08467896278011272, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Priestman, who was born in England, has been banned for one year by FIFA.\", \"from\": 3885, \"to\": 3958, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3912, \"end\": 3919, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.6759367727629646, \"rank\": 0.4793457652205607, \"text\": \"England\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/England_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3953, \"end\": 3957, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA\", \"score\": 0.9999980030863228, \"rank\": 1.996917449239428e-06, \"text\": \"FIFA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FIFA\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"the analyst who flew the drone and an assistant coach have also received the same suspension.\", \"from\": 3959, \"to\": 4052, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"As the leader of the team on the field, I want to take accountability, and I plan to fully cooperate with the investigation,\\\" Priestman said via a statement issued through her legal counsel, Layth Gafoor of Lucentem (a sports and entertainment firm).\", \"from\": 4054, \"to\": 4305, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I fought with every ounce of my being to make this program better, much of which will never be known or understood,\\\" she said, adding: \\\"I wish I could say more, but I will refrain at this time, given the appeals process and the ongoing investigation.\\\"\", \"from\": 4307, \"to\": 4559, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kimberley Woods has been handed her bronze medal after she finished third in the women's kayak single